==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reviviscency
<hw>Rev`i*vis"cen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of reviving, or the
state of being revived; renewal of life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In this age we have a sort of <qex>reviviscence</qex>, not, I
fear, of the power, but of a taste for the power, of the early
times.</q> <rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reviviscent</ent>⟦br⟧
